text.section:
The Strategy shall include a plan for the protection of managed pollinators that provides voluntary best management practices for pesticide users, beekeepers, and landowners and agricultural producers. The protection plan shall support:

Communication between beekeepers and applicators;


Reduction of the risk to pollinators from pesticides;


Increases in pollinator habitat;


Maintenance of existing compliance with state pesticide use requirements;


Identification of needs for further research to promote robust agriculture and apiary industries; and


Identification of additional opportunities for education and outreach on pollinators.
